context:
Add chain field to the invoices and settlements database tables (CEO issue #42 - multi-chain support).

Create a Supabase migration file at supabase/migrations/20260301000001_add_chain_support.sql that:
1. Adds column: ALTER TABLE invoices ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS chain VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'base';
2. Adds column: ALTER TABLE settlements ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS chain VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'base';
3. Adds column: ALTER TABLE settlements ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS chain_id INTEGER;
4. Adds index: CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_invoices_chain ON invoices(chain);
5. Adds index: CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_settlements_chain ON settlements(chain);
6. Adds a comment: COMMENT ON COLUMN invoices.chain IS 'Blockchain network: base, polygon, arbitrum';

Also update backend/src/routes/invoices.ts: in the POST /v1/invoices route, read req.body.chain (default 'base') and include it in the insert. Add validation: if chain is provided and not in ['base','polygon','arbitrum'], return 400 with error 'Unsupported chain'.
